===subject:reply to wendy
===from:Shameeka Beckett
===date:Mon Oct 28  7:46:52 2002
===message:I agree with you on your statement about Roosevelt's New Deal being a saving measure.  In the video "Breadline," the farmers stated how Roosevelt helped them by buying their cows from them, canning the meat, and giving it back to them.  So, in the world of agriculture, I'm sure he was a saving grace.  I feel like he started giving the people hope that there was a light at the end of the tunnel.  Because of Roosevelt, people started having more respect for their government leaders, as well as a little faith.  Restoring confidence in government leaders helped economic recovery in the way that once the people began to trust their leaders again, citizens started to play more active roles in trying to free themselves from the depression.  Jobs were created, regulations were established so that hopefully in the future, this wouldn't happen again.  I also don't agree with the statement Mancil Milligan made about Roosevelt saving the country.  I think he started putting people on the right track to help and fend for themselves, and at the time, he was just what the country needed.
=========yorg=========
