===from:Stephenie Buice
===date:Mon Oct 28 22:00:10 2002
===message:You made some very good points, but I disagree with your statement that the New Deal was intended to help the big farmers the most.  I guess Mr. Rosenburg poses these questions because he knows that one person will view things differently than another.  I believe that the New Deal tried to help the unemployed workers the most.  Sure big farmers, as well as, small farmers benefited but what about the WPA (Work Progress Act)?  The WPA created jobs for many individuals, and it also helped to give other countries a head start out of depression.  I do agree that the depression was not over until WWII, but I believe many people benefited from the New Deal and not just big farmers.
