===subject:Post 2
===from:Jason Odom 
===date:Tue Oct 29 20:48:26 2002
===message:Giving FDR broad executive power was definitely the last resort of the American government. It seemed that no other ideas had worked in jump-starting the American economy, so giving the President the power to impose economic policy was necessary at that point in history. FDR's "New Deal" may not have saved the country, but his forward thinking certainly got the economy headed in the right direction. He realized policies had to be created that would bring faith back to the American people relating to their outlook the future.
=========yorg=========
